<item>
            <title>[LU-18631] lustreapi.h is incompatible with GLib</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18631</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A user-space application using Lustre and GLib would face build issues, making them incompatible.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;foo.c:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
#include &amp;lt;lustre/lustreapi.h&amp;gt;
#include &amp;lt;glib.h&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
$ gcc -I/usr/include/glib-2.0 -I/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/glib-2.0/include -c foo.c 
In file included from /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/glib-2.0/include/glibconfig.h:9,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;from /usr/include/glib-2.0/glib/gtypes.h:34,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;from /usr/include/glib-2.0/glib/galloca.h:34,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;from /usr/include/glib-2.0/glib.h:32,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;from foo.c:4:
/usr/include/glib-2.0/glib/gmacros.h:682:28: error: missing &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;)&apos;&lt;/span&gt; after &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;__has_attribute&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&#160; 682 | #&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; g_macro__has_attribute(fallthrough)
&#160; &#160; &#160; | &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;^~~~~~~~~~~
In file included from foo.c:2:
/usr/include/glib-2.0/glib/gmacros.h:682:28: error: missing binary &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;operator&lt;/span&gt; before token &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;(&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&#160; 682 | #&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; g_macro__has_attribute(fallthrough)
&#160; &#160; &#160; | &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;^~~~~~~~~~~
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is because &lt;tt&gt;lustreapi.h&lt;/tt&gt; redefines the &lt;tt&gt;fallthrough&lt;/tt&gt; attribute:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lustreapi.h:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
#ifndef fallthrough
# &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; defined(__GNUC__) &amp;amp;&amp;amp; __GNUC__ &amp;gt;= 7
# &#160;define fallthrough &#160;__attribute__((fallthrough)) &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* fallthrough */&lt;/span&gt;
# &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
# &#160;define fallthrough &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; {} &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; (0) &#160;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* fallthrough */&lt;/span&gt;
# endif
#endif&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;glib:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
#&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; g_macro__has_attribute(fallthrough)
#define G_GNUC_FALLTHROUGH __attribute__((fallthrough)) \
&#160; GLIB_AVAILABLE_MACRO_IN_2_60
#&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
#define G_GNUC_FALLTHROUGH \
&#160; GLIB_AVAILABLE_MACRO_IN_2_60
#endif&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is preventing to build some user-space tools like Robinhood, which is using both libraries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;gcc: 13.3&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;libglib2.0: 2.80&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
