                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="441091" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 14 Jan 2025 17:50:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is a gcc extension with -Wimplicit-fallthrough. Maybe we can replace it with &lt;em&gt;{&lt;/em&gt;}attribute{&lt;em&gt;}&lt;/em&gt; ((fallthrough)) ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is now a part of C++17 standard.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="441072" author="JIRAUSER18483" created="Tue, 14 Jan 2025 16:45:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is &lt;tt&gt;fallthrough&lt;/tt&gt; a standard keywords in RHEL &amp;gt; 7 ? I don&apos;t think so. It is for the kernel, but not for the user-space. We still need a custom macro, or change the existing &lt;tt&gt;fallthrough;&lt;/tt&gt; to one of the supported keywords, and that will be a pity if they are different between kernel and user-space code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="441064" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 14 Jan 2025 16:19:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Its a RHEL7 gcc version issue. I think we can drop that work around once RHEL7 debug kernel goes away.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="441062" author="JIRAUSER18483" created="Tue, 14 Jan 2025 15:45:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Peter, unfortunately I don&apos;t have a fix for it and I don&apos;t know what it could be. This is a bug report and I&apos;m happy to see what other people think about that problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
